                            <h4>Q6. Is there any application fee, if so, how much? </h4>
                            <p>Yes, there is application processing fee of payable to School of Postgraduate Studies, Ahmadu Bello University Zaria via Remita at any commercial bank in Nigeria. The prospective applicants outside the country tends to have challenges regarding the payment of processing fee (though Remita is now available in some countries e.g. Ghana), where the local currency payment of #10,000 (equivalent to 30 USD) can be made. The university is currently working on this, to ensure that regional/international applicants can pay their processing fee without any difficulty. Based on this, applicants with such challenges can liaise with ACENTDFB so that any issues regarding the processing fee can be handled effectively. </p>

                            <h4>Q7. How do I pay application fee since I am not a Nigerian?</h4>
                            <p>Once you complete your application form, you will be prompted to generate the transaction ID for payment of processing fee. After generating the transaction ID then there are two ways that application processing fee can be paid; the first involves the use of Remita in any commercial banks that have that window/platform as it is available in some ECOWAS countries and the second one may require anyone within the country to make payment on your behalf using local currency (#10,000 which is equivalent to 30 USD) in Nigerian commercial bank via Remita. Note that for payment to be made on your behalf; your username and password need to be made known to that person. </p>

                            <h4>Q8. I am not an anglophone, is there any provision for me to apply?</h4>
                            <p>Yes, Ahmadu Bello University is one of the most culturally diverse learning environment in Nigeria and ACENTDFB can provide English language support courses for Francophone students based on the need either before the start or during the course of their programmes. </p>
                            <h4>Q9. Do I need visa to come to Nigeria?</h4>
                            <p>Once you obtain an admission into our programme, if you are not from any of the ECOWAS countries then you are required to secure a valid visa before entering Nigeria; this can be obtained in Nigerian High Commission/Embassy of your respective countries. In case of regional applicants that are already in Nigeria, ACENTDFB can help facilitate their registration with Nigerian Immigration Services. </p>

